<p><a id="_ftn2292" href="#_ftnref2292" name="_ftn2292" title="">[2292]</a> Most of this is domestic work such as cooking, shopping, cleaning, washing clothes, getting water, and caring for children.&nbsp; <i>See</i> Government of Sierra Leone, Ministry of Development and Economic Planning, Central Statistics Office, <i>The Status of Women and Children in</i> <i>Sierra Leone</i><i>: A Household Survey Report,</i> MICS2, Final Report, November 2000, 61.</p>
<p><a id="_ftn2293" href="#_ftnref2293" name="_ftn2293" title="">[2293]</a> Swedish International Development Agency, <i>Looking Back, Thinking Forward: The Fourth Report on the Implementation of the Agenda for Action Adopted at the First World Congress against Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children in Stockholm, Sweden, on 28 August 1996,</i> 1999-2000, at http://www.ecpat.net/Blueboo2000/index.html on 10/28/01.</p>
